Navigational Map for Chemical Factory
This application assists the chemical factory supervisors to view various Tasks, Gas Sensors, Surveillance Cameras located within the factory through 2D Map (bird view) and Panorama View. Spherical Mercator Projection has been used to locate the supervisor and objects. Supervisor can update the status of a Task, view the Gas readings from the various Gas Sensors via Bluetooth communication and view the live streaming from surveillance cameras. Supervisor can perform zoom & pan operations within the 2D Map and Panoramic View. Audio and Video VOIP calls can be placed to either another supervisor or to the Control Room.

Environment:
    *  Android 4.0, Java 6, Eclipse Helios, Android devices, SVN
Responsibilities:
    *  Architecture of client-server applications ; 
    *  Designed and Implemented localized 2D Map Views with multiple zoom levels ; 
    *  Designed and Implemented loading of 2D Map Tiles on-demand ; 
    *  Designed and Implemented multilevel caching mechanism to load 2D Map tiles ; 
    *  Defined the interaction protocol between client and Gas sensors ;

