MyVerizon Self Care Application (Framework - Pilot Project)
My Verizon Self Care framework provides multiple customer care services to the end users. Using this application user(s) can check minutes and data usage, view account balance, make payments, view various user plans, add/remove features and change their voicemail passwords using their handset without reaching a customer care representative.
Each service is developed using custom XML notation providing ample scope to extend the capabilities of the application without modifying or re-installing the framework. The framework uses its own rendering component which interprets the service XML documents and renders UI on the screen using BUIW.
Environment:
    *  BREW SDK 3.1.5, BREW UIW 2.0, VS2008 (IDE), XML, XSD.
Responsibilities:
    *  Architect for Client application ; 
    *  Definition Cell Grammer using XSD
    *  Lead team of 5 members at client location ; 
    *  Implementation of Cell Renderer component which reads, validates, parses and renders UI and logic specified through XML documents ;

Celltop - On Device Portal
Celltop provides an extensible platform for deploying mobile content, commerce and data services. It serves as a framework for Cells (mini applications), displaying and managing them in a form of mobile phone desktop. Celltop consists of the following five core modules
    *  Font Library supports custom fonts to cover different Font Sizes, specifically to avoid various porting issues on different handsets across various OEMs. Supports changing font color dynamically. ; 
    *  Rainbow Effect provisions to end-users to personalize the look-and-feel of the application by selecting their favorite color and level of brightness. ; 
    *  XML Parser used to represent an XML document in its equivalent DOM Document. ; 
    *    Widget Library supports high-end UI elements and gives rich look-and-feel. ; 
    *    Cell Renderer parses, integrates and renders the XML based Cells in the Celltop environment.
Environment:
    *  J2ME, BlackBerry, WTK 2.4, Eclipse 3.2, XML, Java 1.5.
Responsibilities:
    *  Architect for Client Implementation
    *  Lead team of 10 members ; 
    *  Defined XML Definition for Cell creation using DTD ; 
    *  Designed and Defined Celltop SDK for Cell Development which validates XML documents, collates Images/resources and generates Cell package. ; 
    *  Implementation of custom font library to overcome font problems across various form factors ; 
    *  Defined client-server interaction protocol ; 
    *  Optimized Memory and Performance to support vast range of devices starting from low end to high end devices ; 
    *  Achieved very low footprint to support devices with 64 KB JAR limitation and 512 KB runtime memory

